In order to understand the reasons for dispersancy of soot particles in used engine oil; in addition to ‘used engine oil’, we also need to analyze two variants of soot particles extracted from the used engine oil -namely - the one in which dispersant macromolecules remain attached to the soot particles (referred to as Type-1) and the other in which there are no attached dispersant macromolecules (referred to as Type-2). Now, in order to extract the two aforementioned soot types from used engine oil, we need to understand solution thermodynamics. The interaction energy between the solvent and polymer macromolecule is given by Eq. (1) as371Δε=−K(δs−δp)2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
